Spatially Adjusted Time-varying Reproductive Numbers

For writing R extensions

source("R.R")

I. Point data with cases coordinates

x = dengue$long
y = dengue$lat
t = dengue$date
Rj = calc.Rj(t, x, y)
Rt = calc.Rj(t, adj.sp = F)
image.Rj(Rj)

plot.epi(t)

plot.points(x,y)

plot.points(x,y,base_map=Taiwan)

plot.hex(x, y)

plot.kde(x, y)

plot.Rt(t,list(Rj$Rj)) ####

plot.Rt(t,Rjs = list("Non-adjusted"=Rt$Rj,"Adjusted"=Rj$Rj)) ####

plot.points(x,y,Rj$Rj)

plot.hex(x,y,Rj$Rj)

animate.points(t,x,y,Rj$Rj)

animate.hex(t,x,y,Rj$Rj)

II. Polygon data with cases statistics

covid=GeoLocater(covid19,RndPts)
covid.Rj = calc.Rj(t=covid$date,x=covid$x,y=covid$y,lpdf_GI=GI(5.2,1.5),lpdf_SP=SP(125),CRS_TWD97=T)
plot.Rt(covid$date,list(covid.Rj$Rj)) ####

plot.points(covid$x,covid$y,base_map=Taipei)

plot.polygons(covid$region,Taipei)

animate.polygons(covid$date,covid$region,Taipei)

covid.Tij= ReduceMatrix(covid.Rj$Pij,covid$region)
plot.Tij(covid.Tij,Taipei)
